					<head>Karaite law</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic treatise on the interpretation of the commandments.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="61v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ha-mitsṿot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש המצוות </title>
							<note>
								<p>A large portion, followed by a small portion of a work treating on the differences and points of agreement between bu 'Ali (Abu 'Ali Ḥasan al-Batsri?) and Abu al-Sari (Sahl ben Matsliaḥ al-Imam or ha-Kohen) in the interpretation of commandments.</p>
								<p>Written in Arabic, but the quotations are given in the Hebrew characters.</p>
								<p>Diacritic points are only partially used.</p>
								<p>The title given on both the recto and the verso of folio 2, only partially preserved.</p>
								<p>Folios 2v-13r treat on the festival of the new moon.</p>
								<p>Folios 13r-25r - فصل في سورة الابيب.</p>
								<p>Folios 25v-49v - מחרת השבת.</p>
								<p>Folios 49v-59v - אלחלבים.</p>
								<p>Quotes several Karaite authorities.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Arabic hand of probably 11th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>61 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>203</height>
										<width>177</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>61 folios (+3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of  mostly 10 leaves each. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folio 2 and 58-59 is mutilated.</p>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Slightly wotm-eaten.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="12 15" writtenLines="12 15">
									<p>Hebrew quotations given in Hebrew characters.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Arabic hand of probably 11th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="60r" to="61v"/>due to a different later hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 60r-61v: two fragments of the same work by another hand. The contents of folio 60 coincide with those on folio 42v to 44r.</p>
							<p>Partially illegible owners' entries in Arabic cursive, on a strip of paper, folio 1r, 1v - written by the same hand as folios 2-59. </p>
						</additions>
